# {{NAME}}

A Helios `mean_reversion_v1` strategy built on [`helios-strategy-sdk`](https://pypi.org/project/helios-strategy-sdk/). Scaffolded by `helios scaffold-strategy mean_reversion_v1`.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Install the package + the SDK from PyPI.
pip install -e .

# 2. Backtest your signal against synthetic prices (no env vars required).
helios backtest --strategy src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py --period 90d

# 3. Copy and fill in the on-chain environment.
cp .env.example .env
$EDITOR .env

# 4. Register on Kite testnet + deploy to your VPS.
helios stake top-up --strategy src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py
helios deploy --strategy src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py --target user@host
```

The whole point of writing your own strategy is the signal — open
`src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py` and edit `on_bar`. The runtime layer
(oracle polling, Groth16 proof generation, `executeWithProof` submission)
is in the SDK and does not need to change.

## What the circuit enforces

`mean_reversion_v1.circom` (`Helios.md §10.3`) commits each trade to:

  * `asset_in`, `asset_out` ∈ `asset_universe`
  * `amount_in_usd ≤ max_position_size_usd`
  * `min_amount_out` respects `max_slippage_bps`
  * Direction matches *some* n-sigma threshold (LONG on N-sigma DOWN,
    SHORT on N-sigma UP, EXIT on mean re-cross or stop-loss)
  * `block_window_end - block_window_start ≤ 100`

The **16-bar lookback is fixed** — the circuit's `price_observations[16]`
hard-codes it. Tune `n_sigma_x100`, sizing, and the stop-loss instead.

`n_sigma_x100` and `stop_loss_price_usd` are private witness inputs.
The chain only sees that *some* threshold / stop pair makes the trade
consistent.

## Build with Claude Code

This scaffold is set up so an AI coding agent can iterate on the
signal and ship to the marketplace without changing any Helios code.

In your terminal:

```bash
claude "Open src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py and add a hard stop-loss \
that exits when price drops 4% below entry on a long. Then run \
'helios backtest --strategy src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py --period 90d' \
and report Sharpe + max drawdown vs. the previous run."
```

The repo's [`CLAUDE.md`](https://github.com/emark-cloud/helios/blob/main/CLAUDE.md) is the canonical operational guide for AI agents working on Helios; class invariants live in `Helios.md §10.3`.

